{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"c5elrg6xfbs9jqfrh4kqo2e","title":"Immutable Class","desc":"","updated":1712859749758,"created":1712859683855,"custom":{},"fname":"arch.design.oo.patterns.immutable class","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":".","selfContained":true,"name":"cs"},"contentHash":"8610afd770ae642dc63a702022bc4c8b","links":[{"from":{"fname":"lang.java.lib.string","id":"vqbisdumti23oeq2xk6oml5","vaultName":"cs"},"type":"backlink","position":{"start":{"line":3,"column":24,"offset":168},"end":{"line":3,"column":67,"offset":211},"indent":[]},"value":"arch.design.oo.patterns.immutable class"},{"from":{"fname":"lang.java.lib.classes.wrappers","id":"rhm2ueynmzepd2gxd9tj0sx","vaultName":"cs"},"type":"backlink","position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":27,"offset":894},"end":{"line":16,"column":70,"offset":937},"indent":[]},"value":"arch.design.oo.patterns.immutable class"}],"anchors":{"what-makes-a-class-immutable":{"type":"header","text":"What makes a class immutable?","value":"what-makes-a-class-immutable","line":13,"column":0,"depth":2},"how-to-create-an-immutable-class":{"type":"header","text":"How to create an immutable class","value":"how-to-create-an-immutable-class","line":19,"column":0,"depth":2},"references":{"type":"header","text":"References","value":"references","line":24,"column":0,"depth":2}},"children":[],"parent":"g2xyppezmzmbtru51ncc3zo","data":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"immutable-class\">Immutable Class<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#immutable-class\"></a></h1>\n<p>Cannot be changed (mutated)</p>\n<p>Whenever changed - a new instance is created</p>\n<h2 id=\"what-makes-a-class-immutable\">What makes a class immutable?<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#what-makes-a-class-immutable\"></a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Instance variable is final (value can't be changed)</li>\n<li>class = final - So subclass can't be created</li>\n<li>No setters</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"how-to-create-an-immutable-class\">How to create an immutable class<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#how-to-create-an-immutable-class\"></a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Create <strong>final</strong> class with all <strong>final data members</strong>.</li>\n<li>You can make a class immutable using builder pattern.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"references\">References<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#references\"></a></h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.journaldev.com/1432/java-immutable-class-builder\">Java Immutable Class - Builder Pattern</a></p>\n<hr>\n<strong>Backlinks</strong>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/cs/notes/vqbisdumti23oeq2xk6oml5\">String (cs)</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/cs/notes/rhm2ueynmzepd2gxd9tj0sx\">Wrapper Classes (cs)</a></li>\n</ul>","noteIndex":{"id":"7ncn3al6mmutkhgoesulce9","title":"Computer Science","desc":"","updated":1715103618849,"created":1713296516553,"custom":{"nav_order":0,"permalink":"/"},"fname":"root","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":".","selfContained":true,"name":"cs"},"contentHash":"36faf26c6be438d4aed355d72b55a110","links":[{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"7ncn3al6mmutkhgoesulce9","vaultName":"cs"},"value":"arch","position":{"start":{"line":6,"column":3,"offset":105},"end":{"line":6,"column":11,"offset":113},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"arch"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"7ncn3al6mmutkhgoesulce9","vaultName":"cs"},"value":"paradigm","position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":3,"offset":159},"end":{"line":11,"column":15,"offset":171},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"paradigm"}}],"anchors":{"references":{"type":"header","text":"References","value":"references","line":23,"column":0,"depth":2}},"children":["0xgibr34qhbv1edksyoxakk","t246wcci6dy9lnof7l1os4l","71sipcgr0pdqyxnmntvx28w","6k8qk8m6zofpfla0wr8eajn","szmkrtr9ezx1kg3mzcamb7m","a6m88ijp6ij9aam2ose0k6j","7t5m5bvvkqqmexze4ymednf","4bgqfqpix52j5ek9oawj3lw","ng2w78j1rxy1prvsi6zc9j3","q1uj4uy5892ahhlgrn1wi7m","qneto